e gravitational field and an infinitesimal detector, and develop a\nmicroaveraging procedure that renders the process gauge-invariant. The exchange\nof nonspatial angular momentum (i.e., moment of energy) is also analyzed,\nleading us to conclude that a gravitational wave can displace the center of\nmass of the detector; this conclusion is also confirmed by a first principles\ntreatment of the system. Finally, we discuss...\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Oct 2012 16:28:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-10-03"}
